fuzz_open_mem: infinite loop / very-slow parse in RAR5 header path.
Discovered on the first 30-second smoke run of the libFuzzer harness.
Stack (libFuzzer timeout signal): dmc_unrar_rar5_read_file_header ->
dmc_unrar_rar5_read_number -> dmc_unrar_io_read_uint8.
Likely cause: malformed extra-field walk driving the RAR5 header
parser into a bounded-but-expensive loop that exceeds 25 seconds on
a 129-byte input. Needs fix + regression test once a timeout-aware
runner (fork + alarm) is added to runner.c.
